"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527612\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527612\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 11, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104fpm1665702867955.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fpm1665702867955.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fpm1665702867955.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"fpm1665702867955\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n         \n Uniface Desktop Applications \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface desktop applications are client/server applications, in which an application shell and form components run locally. Usually, service and report components run on a remote server.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fpm1665702867955__p_d23771e1_d23772e1_d23773e1\">Most desktop applications run on Windows, but they can also run as character-based applications on any supported platform.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fpm1665702867955__p_d23774e1_d23775e1_d23776e1\">The user interface of desktop applications consists of:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fpm1665702867955__li_d11825e1_d11826e1_d11827e1\">An application shell, which initializes the application and defines the window in which it runs (or the layout used in character-based applications). For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yye1705472567076.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yye1705472567076.html\" title=\"An application shell is the first object that is executed when a Windows or character mode application is started. It determines how the application is initialized and the first form component that is displayed.\">Application Shells for Desktop Applications</a>.\n           </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fpm1665702867955__li_d11828e1_d11829e1_d11830e1\">Form components that provide an interactive user interface in which users can display and edit data. Forms support a rich set of widgets and layout objects, such as area frames and split bars, for building an attractive and flexible user interface. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"usl1704692305727.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/usl1704692305727.html\" title=\"Form components provide the user interface for Uniface desktop applications. They are always executed on the client system and can be modal (form retains focus until it is closed) or non-modal (users can switch focus to other forms).\">Forms</a>.\n           </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fpm1665702867955__li_d11831e1_d11832e1_d11833e1\">Global objects, such as menus and panels for use in forms and application shells, messages for user feedback, and drag-and-drop formats. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bgv1665702551096.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bgv1665702551096.html\" title=\"A global object is a reusable, technology-independent object that is centrally stored and available to all components running on a given host, regardless of the deployment environment.\">Global Objects</a>.\n           </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fpm1665702867955__li_d11834e1_d11835e1_d11836e1\">Report components, which retrieve data and print reports. Headers, footers, and break frames provide print-specific functionality. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ccr1704692448139.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ccr1704692448139.html\" title=\"Reports are components for generating output—they have no user interface and cannot update the database. They make use of headers, footers, and break frames to format data and control printing.\">Reports</a>.\n           </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fpm1665702867955__p_d23777e1_d23778e1_d23779e1\">Other application processing can be provided by service components that are activated by other components.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fpm1665702867955__p_d23780e1_d23781e1_d23782e1\">To start the application, the user runs the application shell using the Uniface executable (<span class=\"ph filepath\">uniface.exe</span>). The application shell activates the first form and passes control to it.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ods1692009951805.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface Applications</a><p>Uniface applications are typically mission-critical enterprise applications that use and maintain data stored in one or more databases, files, or other data resources. They may integrate with all kinds of non-Uniface applications, and they can be deployed on a wide variety of platforms.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qjd1665702751029.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>How a Desktop Application Works</a><p>A Uniface desktop application is a traditional client/server application which can run on a local machine with access to remote functionality when needed.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527612\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527612\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Uniface Desktop Applications Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 11, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uniface Desktop Applications Uniface desktop applications are client/server applications, in which an application shell and form components run locally. Usually, service and report components run on a remote server. Most desktop applications run on Windows, but they can also run as character-based applications on any supported platform. The user interface of desktop applications consists of: An application shell, which initializes the application and defines the window in which it runs (or the layout used in character-based applications). For more information, see Application Shells for Desktop Applications . Form components that provide an interactive user interface in which users can display and edit data. Forms support a rich set of widgets and layout objects, such as area frames and split bars, for building an attractive and flexible user interface. For more information, see Forms . Global objects, such as menus and panels for use in forms and application shells, messages for user feedback, and drag-and-drop formats. For more information, see Global Objects . Report components, which retrieve data and print reports. Headers, footers, and break frames provide print-specific functionality. For more information, see Reports . Other application processing can be provided by service components that are activated by other components. To start the application, the user runs the application shell using the Uniface executable ( uniface.exe ). The application shell activates the first form and passes control to it. Related Links Uniface Applications Uniface applications are typically mission-critical enterprise applications that use and maintain data stored in one or more databases, files, or other data resources. They may integrate with all kinds of non-Uniface applications, and they can be deployed on a wide variety of platforms. How a Desktop Application Works A Uniface desktop application is a traditional client/server application which can run on a local machine with access to remote functionality when needed. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}